UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1332
1 AN ACT proposing to create a new section of the Constitution of Kentucky relating
2 to citizenship requirements for state and local elected officials.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 Section 1. Are you in favor of amending the Constitution of Kentucky by
5 adding a new section to establish that a person shall not be eligible to be elected or serve
6 in certain state and local offices unless he or she is a citizen of the United States, and has
7 not been a citizen or national of any country other than the United States, at the time of
8 election or appointment and for the immediately preceding eighteen (18) years, as stated
9 below?
10 SECTION 2. IT IS PROPOSED THAT A NEW SECTION BE ADDED TO
11 THE CONSTITUTION OF KENTUCKY TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
12 In addition to the requirements of Sections 32, 72, 91, 92, 100, and 122, and any
13 other Section of this Constitution, a person shall not be eligible to be elected or
14 appointed to any elected office of the Commonwealth of Kentucky, including but not
15 limited to the offices of Governor, Lieutenant Governor, Attorney General, Secretary of
16 State, Auditor of Public Accounts, Treasurer, Commissioner of Agriculture, member of
17 the General Assembly, justice or judge of any court of the Court of Justice, county
18 officer, or any other statewide, judicial, legislative, or local elected office established
19 under this Constitution or by law, unless that person, both at the time of election or
20 appointment and for the duration of his or her term of office:
21 1. Is a citizen of the United States;
22 2. Has been a citizen of the United States for at least eighteen (18) years
23 immediately preceding the election or appointment; and
24 3. Is not, and has not been for the eighteen (18) years immediately preceding
25 his or her election or appointment, a citizen or national of any foreign state or country.
26 This section shall not apply to offices of the United States government.
27 Section 3. This amendment shall be submitted to the voters of the
